                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9221: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sokobin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-07T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 7, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your August 7, 11 a.m., and previous on same subject. By way of caution,
                    Department feels that American official agencies should be on guard against
                    giving any impression of attempting to influence Chinese authorities in relation
                    to questions of military operations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
